            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>ΗΡΑ[- -] Abbreviation of the personal name, so ownership or commercial (producer's or merchant's mark?). 
                    Or sacred property of Hera? <!--Should be compared to name inscribed on amphora from Beliaus (N. Black Sea),
                    late 4th/early 3rd century - SEG 49:1026,2 from Arkheolohiia (1999.1) pp. 177-183
                    Graffiti (indication of capacity and owner's name?).  Amphora; inscription (a) on the rim:graffito a.1 ΨΔ = 60 [how do they get this number?], 
                    (b) below the rim: graffito b.1	Ἡρᾶς.  -->  
                    The name is attested as stamp of the eponym Baton and the fabricant Heras.  
                    Thasian amphora handle. Found in Histria, published: Histria VIII,1 88.
                    Scythia Minor [Thasos] — Istros-Histria — ca. 356-343 BC.  1	Θασι(․ν). Βά|τ[ω]|ν. Ἡρᾶ|ς.</p>
            </div>
